evaluation.response:
I totally get it. It can feel really overwhelming to be constantly connected and bombarded with messages and notifications. Taking a step back and setting boundaries can be really helpful in managing that feeling.

Deleting your socials and turning your phone off at night are both totally valid ways to take care of yourself and set those boundaries. It's okay to take time for yourself and prioritize your own needs.

If you feel like you need to disappear, that is okay. Disengaging from social media can be really helpful in regaining your sense of self-worth and identity outside of online platforms.&#x20;
